com.edatasource.receipts.model.ecommerce

Class EcommerceReceipt

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.edatasource.receipts.model.Receipt
      • com.edatasource.receipts.model.ecommerce.EcommerceReceipt

  • public class EcommerceReceipt
extends Receipt
    Class which represents an ecommerce order receipt.

    An ecommerce receipt is made up of a receipt, billing information, shipping information, and one-to-many shipments. It is very important that callers call addShipment(EcommerceShipment) when adding a new shipment to ensure that the associations are setup correctly.

      • getShipping

        public Address getShipping()
        Returns the primary shipping address for this receipt.

        This shipping addresses have been moved to the "Shipments" object to support shipping to multiple addresses. But to ensure backward compatibility with the UI this method must still be left here.
        This method will check to see if the shipping address has been called once, if not, it will then load in the first non-null shipping address from the shipments collection. Perfect solution? Nope. But, it's good enough for the current UI.

        What does all this mean?
        Data analytics should be performed against the EcommerceShipment collection instead of this method.
        Returns:
        Primary shipping address

        public void setNumberOfItems(int numberOfItems)
        Overrides the automatic calculation for the total number of items and sets the total number of items to the specified value.

        In order to allow the receipt framework to automatically calculate the total number of items, based upon the shipments within this receipt, leave this value at zero (0).

        Parameters:

      • getShippingMethod

        public java.lang.String getShippingMethod()
        Returns a comma-separated list of the shipping methods.

        Shipping methods are now located on the EcommerceShipment object.
        However, to facilitate backward compatibility with the UI this method will automatically comma-separate each of the shipping methods and return the unique set.

        Returns:
        String comma-separated list of shipping methods
